From 1e01761885ffa7799a448c72e1e5eeda50c1bf29 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: t <t@t>
Date: Thu, 18 Jun 2026 07:01:04 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] refactor(skills): canonical UPPER_SNAKE_CASE everywhere
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Skill identity is now the canonical UPPER_SNAKE_CASE key
(SKILL_CATALOG_ORDER / ALL_SKILL_KEYS). Localized names exist only at the
render boundary via getSkillDisplayName(key).

Data (data/**/*.json):
- armor_mods.json, uniq_armor_mods.json, weapon_mods.json: 'Repair' /
  '?Repair' / 'Repair ' / 'Science' -> 'REPAIR' / 'SCIENCE' (single source).
- robot/{robotarms,robotbody,robotheads,robotlegs,weapon_mods_assaultron_laser}.json:
  'Repair' / 'Science' -> 'REPAIR' / 'SCIENCE'.
- traits.json: forcedSkills 'energy_weapons'|'science'|'repair'|'small_guns'
  -> 'ENERGY_WEAPONS'|'SCIENCE'|'REPAIR'|'SMALL_GUNS';
  skillModifiers key 'survival' -> 'SURVIVAL'.
- Empty '' kept (means 'no skill required').

Domain (domain/characterCreation.js):
- ALL_SKILLS[i].name is the canonical key (was: Russian display name).
- Dropped import of ruCharacterScreen — no locale literals in pure logic.

Display layer:
- characterScreenI18n.js: getSkillDisplayName(SKILL_KEY) — canonical-only
  input, no RU_SKILL_TO_KEY alias bridge.
- All trait modals (Brotherhood, OutcastBrotherhood, Minuteman, Ghoul,
  Survivor, VaultDweller) now hold canonical SKILL keys in
  SELECTABLE_SKILLS / forcedSkills / skillModifiers / goodSoulGroup, and
  render labels via getSkillDisplayName(key).
- CharacterScreen.js: GOOD_SOUL_SKILL_KEYS is the single constant, no more
  getGoodSoulSkillNames() locale mapping; render via getSkillDisplayName.

WeaponsAndArmorScreen:
- Dropped 17-line SKILL_ALIASES bridge (RU/EN/UPPER fan-out). findSkillValue
  now compares against canonical key directly.
- TRAITS['Пехотинец'] -> findTraitById('ncr-infantryman').

Persistence (back-compat):
- CharacterContext.loadCharacter runs migrateSkillsToCanonical() on legacy
  saves that stored skill.name as Russian display strings — one-time
  rewrite to UPPER_SNAKE_CASE on load. After this PR the bridge may be
  removed in a follow-up once all live saves are migrated.

Contract test (domain/contract.skills.test.js):
- Asserts every skill reference in data/**/*.json is in ALL_SKILL_KEYS
  (or empty '').
- Asserts no Russian skill display literals appear in code logic
  (i18n catalogs excluded — that's the only allowed home for locale strings).

This eliminates the five-form chaos: 'REPAIR' / 'Repair' / 'repair' /
'?Repair' / 'Ремонт' all collapsed to canonical 'REPAIR'.
